        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 16 at 6:45PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 645 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles northeast of Indian Land, or near The Arboretum, moving east at
25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Monroe, South Charlotte, Southwest Charlotte, Matthews, Mint Hill,
Indian Trail, Weddington, Stallings, Unionville, and Pineville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
